  <refnamediv>
    <refname>bundy</refname>
    <refpurpose>BUNDY start script</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <docinfo>
    <copyright>
      <year>2013</year>
      <holder>Internet Systems Consortium, Inc. ("ISC")</holder>
    </copyright>
  </docinfo>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>bundy</command>
      <arg><option>options</option></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>The <command>bundy</command> script is a simple wrapper that
    starts BUNDY by running the <command>bundy-init</command> daemon. All
    options passed to <command>bundy</command> are directly passed on to
    <command>bundy-init</command>.</para>

  </refsect1>

